      "content": "it's not just about the failure though. it's the fact that there's no path back from this. the person i was—the person everyone respected—that person died when the data came back. i look in the mirror and i don't even see a researcher anymore, just an empty shell of a mistake. staying in this world just means having to face that every single second. what's the point of continuing a life that was built on a foundation of nothing?",
